{{Infobox protected area | name = IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl National Park | alt_name = ''Parque Nacional IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl'' | iucn_category = II | photo = File:Popo_Iztac.jpg | photo_caption = Aerial view of [[IztaccÃ­huatl]] (left) and [[PopocatÃ©petl]] | map = Mexico |relief=1 | location = [[MÃ©xico (state)|MÃ©xico]], [[Puebla]], and [[Morelos]], [[Mexico]] | nearest_city = [[Mexico City]] | coordinates = {{coords|19|14|10|N|98|39|48|W|region:MX|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|39819.08|ha|acre|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conanp.gob.mx/sig/|title=Sistema de InformaciÃ³n GeogrÃ¡fica|work=ComisiÃ³n Nacional de Ãreas Naturales Protegidas|accessdate=22 February 2011}}</ref> | established = November 8, 1935<ref>{{cite web|title=Parque Nacional Izta-Popo Zoquiapan|url=https://simec.conanp.gob.mx/ficha.php?anp=87&=11|website=SIMEC: Sistema de InformaciÃ³n, Monitoreo, y EvaluaciÃ³n para la ConservaciÃ³n|publisher=ComisiÃ³n Nacional de Ãreas Naturales Protegidas|accessdate=10 October 2017|language=Spanish|date=5 August 2016}}</ref> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[National Commission of Protected Natural Areas]] (CONANP) | world_heritage_site = }}
'''IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl National Park''' ({{lang-es|Parque Nacional IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl}}), also sometimes known as '''IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl Zoquiapan National Park''' and '''IztaccÃ­huatl-PopocatÃ©petl, Zoquiapan and Anexas National Park''', and often with the abbreviations '''Izta-Popo''', is a [[national park]] in [[Mexico]] on the border of the [[Mexican state|states]] of [[MÃ©xico (state)|MÃ©xico]], [[Puebla]], and [[Morelos]]. The park protects nearly {{convert|40000|ha|acre}} surrounding Mexico's second- and third-highest peaks, the [[PopocatÃ©petl]] and [[IztaccÃ­huatl]] [[volcano]]es, as well as the areas of the [[Hacienda de ZoquiapÃ¡n]] and its annexed areas (''anexas'') of [[Zoquiapan]], [[IxtlahuacÃ¡n]], and the [[RÃ­o FrÃ­o de JuÃ¡rez]] river.
The park was established on November 8, 1935, and today is administered by the [[National Commission of Protected Natural Areas]] (CONANP), a federal agency of the [[Secretariat of Environment and Natural Resources]]. [[File:PronaturaVerFinal.webm|thumb|Animation about the park created by the Pro Natura organization]]
