This is a '''list''' of '''mining areas''' in '''Colombia'''.<ref name=MinDatList>[https://www.mindat.org/lsearch.php?from=nsearch&loc=Colombia List of mining areas, Colombia] at [[Mindat.org|Mindat]].org</ref> The [[mineral industry of Colombia]] is large and diverse; the country occupies the first place in mining areas per surface area in the world. In pre-Columbian <!-- no typo; refers to pre-Columbus! --> times, mining of gold, silver, copper, emeralds, salt, coal and other minerals was already widespread. Precious metals as gold,<ref name=UPMEgold/> and silver,<ref name=UPMEsilver/> platinum, nickel and coltan are located in different areas throughout the country. Colombia is the first producer of [[Colombian emeralds|emeralds]] and as per February 2017 occupied a ninth position in the production of coal, produced in almost all of the departments of the country.<ref name=UPMEcoal/><ref name=WorldAtlasCoal>{{cite web |date=21 February 2017 |title=The Top 10 Coal Producers Worldwide |url=http://www.worldatlas.com/articles/the-top-10-coal-producers-worldwide.html |publisher=World Atlas |accessdate=2017-04-09}}</ref> Platinum is mostly found in the [[Cordillera Occidental (Colombia)|Western]] and [[Cordillera Central (Colombia)|Central Ranges]] of the Colombian [[Andes]].<ref name=UPMEplatinum/> Copper said to have been produced during colonial and later times apparently came from small shoots which may have been worked primarily for their gold content.<ref name=Singewald_p54>Singewald, 1949, p.54</ref> The largest gold mine in Colombia is scheduled to start operations in [[BuriticÃ¡]], [[Antioquia Department|Antioquia]].<ref name=EspectadorBuritica/><ref name=PortafolioBuritica/>

Frequently, there are conflicts between the potential mining activities and the [[indigenous peoples in Colombia|indigenous communities]] in the country, especially in the eastern, sparsely populated departments of [[Vichada Department|Vichada]], [[GuainÃ­a Department|GuanÃ­a]], [[Guaviare Department|Guaviare]] and [[VaupÃ©s Department|VaupÃ©s]].<ref name=MapaResguardosMinerales>{{es}} [http://geoactivismo.org//wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ti_minmetpre10.png Mapa de Territorios IndÃ­genas y Minerales Preciosos]</ref><ref name=Semana>{{es}} [http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/la-guerra-coltan/110119-3 La guerra por el coltÃ¡n] - [[Semana (magazine)|Semana]]</ref>

