'''SpaÄva''' is a geographic microregion in [[Croatia]]. It is located in the south-western part of [[Syrmia]]&mdash;the latter being divided by Croatia and [[Serbia]]&mdash;and the southeastern part of [[Slavonia]] [[List of regions of Croatia|macroregion of Croatia]], around [[SpaÄva (river)|SpaÄva]] river and river [[Studva]]. The region is famous for its biggest contiguous [[oak]] ([[Quercus robur]]) forest in the [[Europe]].<ref name="HrastLAG">{{cite web|url=http://www.ar-hrast.hr/default.aspx?id=12213 | title=Approved 10 projects over HRK million worth | date=27 April 2016 | author= | publisher= | page= | language= | format= | accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Faculty of Science">{{cite web|url=http://digre.pmf.unizg.hr/1573/ | title=The Impact of SpaÄvanski Bazen of Economic Development in Vukovar-Srijem County | date=2014 | author=Ika LuciÄ | publisher=[[Faculty of Science, University of Zagreb]] | page= | language= | format= | accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref> Wood industry based in SpaÄva basin is important in the economical life of [[Vukovar-Srijem County]]. The major settlement in the region is the town of [[Otok, Vukovar-Srijem County|Otok]].<ref name="Faculty of Science"/>

